# Leptos UI Rules

## WASM Gotchas

- No `println!` — use `web_sys::console::log_1` or `leptos::logging::log!`
- No `std::time` — use `gloo_timers` or `web_sys::Performance`
- Async data: use `create_local_resource`, not `spawn_local`
- Errors: call `report_error_with_toast()`, not just `console::error_1()`

## UI Responsibility Boundary

**Frontend:** rendering, layout, user input, API calls, SSE streaming, client-side filtering/pagination.

**Never in UI:** cryptography, policy evaluation, receipt generation, determinism enforcement, core business logic.

## Layout Primitives

- **SplitPanel** — list/detail layouts (Training, Models, Policies).
- **VirtualList** — >200 items; **CappedList** — 50–200 with "Show more"; **Direct render** — <50 items.
- **ErrorDisplay** — with `on_retry` when refetch is available.

## Liquid Glass (dist/glass.css)

| Tier | Usage        | Blur  | Alpha |
|------|--------------|-------|-------|
| 1    | headers, nav | 9.6px | 70%   |
| 2    | cards, panels| 12px  | 78%   |
| 3    | dialogs      | 15.6px| 85%   |

Borders: 1px hsla white 0.30. Motion: state-change only.

## Performance

- Avoid `.get()` inside render loops; extract once before iterating.
- Use `Memo::new` for derived chart/expensive data, not `Signal::derive`.
